What is Cygwin?

Cygwin is a tool that:

ğŸ‘‰ Makes Windows behave like Linux
ğŸ‘‰ Gives you a Linux terminal (bash) on Windows

Why Is Cygwin Used?

Some engineering tools (like Altair tools) were originally built for:

Linux

UNIX systems

So they need:

Bash shell

Linux commands

Unix-style scripts

Windows does not support these by default.

So we use Cygwin.

Why Cygwin in Altair / HyperWorks?

When you install:

Altair HyperWorks

It uses:

Shell scripts

Environment scripts

Unix commands internally

For example:

uname -r
cygcheck -V
which hwdesktop


These are Linux-style commands.

